      ],
      "response": {
        "text": "The first train travels for 1 hour before the second train leaves. In that hour, it covers 60 miles. So, when the second train leaves, the distance between them is 195 - 60 = 135 miles. The combined speed of the two trains is 60 + 80 = 140 mph. To cover 135 miles at 140 mph, it takes 135/140 = 0.964 hours. Converting this to minutes gives 0.964 * 60 = 57.86 minutes. Therefore, the trains meet at 10:57.86 a.m., which is approximately 11:00 a.m.",
